headline: UPS, Temu’s Irish Entities Locked in $44 Million Dispute
summary: The Dublin-based arms of UPS and Temu’s parent company, Whaleco Inc., are facing off over unpaid delivery bills related to the Chinese-founded e-tailer’s small-package shipments.

headline: Teamsters union sues UPS to block buyout offer to delivery drivers
summary: UPS is preparing a second voluntary buyout offer for parcel delivery drivers. The Teamsters union has gone to court to force UPS to withdraw the program on the grounds that it doesn’t adequately compensate drivers and undermines the union. The post Teamsters union sues UPS to block buyout offer to delivery drivers appeared first on FreightWaves.

headline: Local Business Owner Celebrates New Venture in Cornelius, North Carolina with Opening of Their Third PostalAnnex--Offering Shipping and More Office Services
summary: Annex Brands, Inc., one of the leading franchisors in the packing, shipping and office services industries, is excited to announce the opening of its newest PostalAnnex location in Cornelius, NC to new owner, Ajay Guthi. This new PostalAnnex, formerly known as Postmarked, is Ajay's third PostalAnnex location and is set to offer a wide range of essential shipping and office services to the local community, making it easier to get more done in one stop.

headline: Teamsters Challenge UPS Driver Buyouts And Raise Questions On Labor Risk
summary: Teamsters Union has filed a legal challenge against United Parcel Service (NYSE:UPS) over a new driver buyout program. The union alleges UPS violated the National Master Agreement by introducing a second, unauthorized buyout and seeking direct deals with drivers. The Teamsters argue that the program encourages drivers to waive union rights and could cause irreparable harm to union representation.
